From 4847e6c1f2727903b0050b692ce9934ebc003571 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: maoxiaochuan <maoxiaochuan@loongson.cn>
Date: Sun, 9 Mar 2025 09:50:05 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 329/376] FROMEXT: LOONGARCH64_NOSIMD: hugetlb:fix build error
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

the error message is as follow:

../arch/loongarch/mm/mmap.c: In function ‘arch_get_unmapped_area_common’:
../arch/loongarch/mm/mmap.c:69:35: error: implicit declaration of function ‘huge_page_mask_align’; did you mean ‘huge_page_mask’? [-Werror=implicit-function-declaration]
   69 |                 info.align_mask = huge_page_mask_align(filp);
      |                                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                                   huge_page_mask
cc1: some warnings being treated as errors

code sync for linux-6.13

Signed-off-by: maoxiaochuan <maoxiaochuan@loongson.cn>

Link: https://gitee.com/open-loongarch/linux-6.12/commit/b679601af647ebf15b177bd7e33bf3a52512af3c
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 include/linux/hugetlb.h | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/linux/hugetlb.h b/include/linux/hugetlb.h
index 3897f4492e1f..28a832ea2c95 100644
--- a/include/linux/hugetlb.h
+++ b/include/linux/hugetlb.h
@@ -1041,6 +1041,11 @@ void hugetlb_unregister_node(struct node *node);
  */
 bool is_raw_hwpoison_page_in_hugepage(struct page *page);
 
+static inline unsigned long huge_page_mask_align(struct file *file)
+{
+	return PAGE_MASK & ~huge_page_mask(hstate_file(file));
+}
+
 #else	/* CONFIG_HUGETLB_PAGE */
 struct hstate {};
 
-- 
